    <title>OpenAI CTO Mira Murati is leaving</title>
    <content type="html">  

    &lt;figure&gt;
      &lt;img alt="OpenAI CTO Mira Murati speaking during the company’s Spring update, with an image of the GPT store in the background." src="https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/BbTpR4JC3O0BqWhbAGY8ZCZW4L0=/0x0:1527x1018/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73610467/Screenshot_2024_05_13_at_12.06.39_PM.0.png" /&gt;
        &lt;figcaption&gt;Screenshot: YouTube&lt;/figcaption&gt;
    &lt;/figure&gt;

  &lt;p id="LftqLJ"&gt;OpenAI CTO &lt;a href="https://fortune.com/longform/openai-mira-murati-chatgpt-dalle-3-generative-ai-agi/"&gt;Mira Murati&lt;/a&gt; is leaving the company, &lt;a href="https://x.com/miramurati/status/1839025700009030027"&gt;she announced on Wednesday&lt;/a&gt;. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p id="fZjyya"&gt;“I’m stepping away because I want to create the time and space to do my own exploration,” she wrote in a post on X. “For now, my primary focus is doing everything in my power to ensure a smooth transition, maintaining the momentum we’ve built.”&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p id="b29S6m"&gt;This comes almost a year after a boardroom coup shook the AI startup and temporarily ousted CEO Sam Altman, leaving Murati as its temporary leader. Prior to OpenAI, Murati worked at Tesla on its AI efforts.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div id="rqFJDX"&gt;
&lt;blockquote class="twitter-tweet" data-dnt="true" align="center"&gt;
&lt;p lang="en" dir="ltr"&gt;I shared the following note with the OpenAI team today. &lt;a href="https://t.co/nsZ4khI06P"&gt;pic.twitter.com/nsZ4khI06P&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;— Mira Murati (@miramurati) &lt;a href="https://twitter.com/miramurati/status/1839025700009030027?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw"&gt;September 25, 2024&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;


&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p id="PoQc1M"&gt;We’ve pasted Murati’s full memo below:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p id="zjRFTN"&gt;Hi all,&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p id="kop9M8"&gt;I have something to share with you....&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
